President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Mindy Brashears to be the Under Secretary for Food Safety at the Department of Agriculture. Dr. Brashears is a Professor of Food Safety and Food Microbiology at Texas Tech University. Her research focuses on improving food safety standards and evaluating interventions in pre- and post-harvest environments. She has also led international research teams to set up sustainable agriculture systems in impoverished areas. President Trump has also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to the President's Council on Sports, Fitness, and Nutrition.